<paragraph id="8BA2CB6BFFF5A126D7914679A8F4F87D" blockId="12.[151,1437,1817,1986]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFF5A126D7914679A833F88D" bold="true" box="[199,286,1817,1842]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFF5A126D6794679A898F88D" box="[303,437,1817,1842]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 50" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1725,1748]" captionTargetBox="[234,1357,193,1696]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1704]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 50. Stigmella species 610. 44, 46, habitat, Vilcabamba, S of Loja, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 1800 m; 45, host-plant Baccharis obtusifolia Kunth; 47, 48, leaf-mines; 49, pupa, ventral view; 50, same, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261796/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
Figs 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF5A126D63F467AA898F88D" box="[361,437,1817,1842]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" value="49.5">49, 50</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head: palpi golden cream; frontal tuft ochre-brown; collar and scape golden cream to yellowish cream; antenna longer than half the length of forewing; flagellum with approx. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF5A126D3EA465EADF5F8E9" box="[1212,1240,1854,1878]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" value="30.0">30</number>
segments (n= 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF5A126D2D5465EACA0F8E9" box="[1411,1421,1854,1878]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" value="1.0">1</number>
), yellowish grey, glossy.Thorax and tegula golden cream. Forewing golden cream except small fuscous spot at base and fuscous apical ¼; cilia brownish cream to golden cream. Abdomen dark brown on upper side, golden cream on uderside (also see Remarks).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF629BE3FFF4A127D7C14600AB55F80B" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261797/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" targetBox="[249,1406,208,1854]" targetPageId="13">
