, not belonging to the type-series; 54, 
<emphasis id="B9691779FFF4A127D6B546FEA8DBF80C" box="[483,502,1950,1971]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">S.</emphasis>
species 609.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA2CB6BFFF7A124D79141F7ABDCFEFF" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFF7A124D79141F7A8BDFF0F" bold="true" box="[199,400,151,176]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFF7A124D6F341F7A8D0FF0F" box="[421,509,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1888,1911]" captionTargetBox="[249,1406,208,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 54. Female genitalia of Stigmella species feeding on Baccharis (ZMUC). 51, S. species 610; 52, S. latifoliae Remeikis, Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., not belonging to the type-series; 53, S. baccharicola Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., not belonging to the type-series; 54, S. species 609." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261797/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF7A124D68841F7A8D0FF0F" box="[478,509,151,176]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
). Total length about 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF7A124D5A141F7AA0CFF0F" box="[759,801,151,176]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="660.0">660</number>
µm. Abdominal apex broad (
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF7A124D3D541F7ADCBFF0F" box="[1155,1254,151,176]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="132.5" valueMax="135.0" valueMin="130.0">130–135</number>
µm), distinctly truncate. Broad apophyses anteriores slightly longer or equal to very narrow apophyses posteriores. Vestibulum relatively broad, without sclerites. Accessory sac very large and folded. Ductus spermathecae narrow, with 1.5 coils (chitinized convolution) (see 
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFF7A124D57A4064ABAFFEA2" box="[556,642,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1888,1911]" captionTargetBox="[249,1406,208,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 54. Female genitalia of Stigmella species feeding on Baccharis (ZMUC). 51, S. species 610; 52, S. latifoliae Remeikis, Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., not belonging to the type-series; 53, S. baccharicola Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., not belonging to the type-series; 54, S. species 609." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261797/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF7A124D5324064ABAFFEA2" box="[612,642,260,285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
, enlarged). Corpus bursae round, covered with numerous comb-like pectinations but without signa (see 
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFF7A124D5754047AB59FEFF" box="[547,628,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1888,1911]" captionTargetBox="[249,1406,208,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 54. Female genitalia of Stigmella species feeding on Baccharis (ZMUC). 51, S. species 610; 52, S. latifoliae Remeikis, Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., not belonging to the type-series; 53, S. baccharicola Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., not belonging to the type-series; 54, S. species 609." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261797/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF7A124D5004047AB59FEFF" box="[598,628,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
, enlarged).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA2CB6BFFF7A124D791402CA9C5FD82" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFF7A124D791402CA867FEDA" bold="true" box="[199,330,332,357]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Bionomics.</emphasis>
Larvae mine in leaves (
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFF7A124D537402CABC5FEDB" box="[609,744,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 50" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1725,1748]" captionTargetBox="[234,1357,193,1696]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1704]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 50. Stigmella species 610. 44, 46, habitat, Vilcabamba, S of Loja, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 1800 m; 45, host-plant Baccharis obtusifolia Kunth; 47, 48, leaf-mines; 49, pupa, ventral view; 50, same, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261796/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
Figs 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF7A124D5CA402CABC5FEDB" box="[668,744,332,356]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="47.48">47, 48</number>
</figureCitation>
). Host-plant: 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB0E8FFF7A124D4D3402CADEAFEDA" authority="Kunth" authorityName="Kunth" box="[901,1223,332,357]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obtusifolia">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFF7A124D4D3402CAD55FEDA" box="[901,1144,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Baccharis obtusifolia</emphasis>
Kunth
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB0E8FFF7A124D381402CAC78FEDB" box="[1239,1365,332,356]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFF7A124D238402CA99AFE37" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 50" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1725,1748]" captionTargetBox="[234,1357,193,1696]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1704]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 50. Stigmella species 610. 44, 46, habitat, Vilcabamba, S of Loja, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 1800 m; 45, host-plant Baccharis obtusifolia Kunth; 47, 48, leaf-mines; 49, pupa, ventral view; 50, same, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261796/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF7A124D7C1400FA99AFE37" box="[151,183,367,392]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="45.0">45</number>
</figureCitation>
). Egg on upper side of leaf. Larvae pale green with brownish green intestine and pale brown head; mine in February. Leaf-mine long, starting on underside (which is unusual for the most of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB0E8FFF7A124D31540F4ADFAFE12" box="[1091,1239,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nepticulidae</taxonomicName>
), occasionally on upper side of leaf-blade as a long narrow gallery filled with dark brown frass; later mining continues on upper side of leaf-blade only; leaf-mine contorted and abruptly widening, with central line of black frass. Larval exit slit on upper side of the leaf. Cocoon pale grey-beige; length 2.6–3.2 mm, maximal width 1.3–1.8 mm. Adults emerged in March.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30798E0FFF7A124D7914327AAC9FD3A" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA2CB6BFFF7A124D7914327AAC9FD3A" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFF7A124D7914327A874FDDF" bold="true" box="[199,345,583,608]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFF7A124D63E4327A880FDDF" box="[360,429,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1980,2002]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1956]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1959]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Current records of Stigmella species feeding on plants from the genus Baccharis L." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261788/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF7A124D6CB4328A880FDDF" box="[413,429,584,608]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). This species occurs in the equatorial Andes (
<collectingCountry id="F30A8BFBFFF7A124D4E04327AD3AFDDF" box="[950,1047,583,608]" name="Ecuador" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
) on rocky slopes at altitudes about 
<quantity id="4CE5668EFFF7A124D7C1430CA9C1FD3B" box="[151,236,620,644]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" unit="m" value="1800.0">1800 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFF7A124D7AD430CA863FD3B" box="[251,334,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 38" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1551,1574]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,195,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1530]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 38. Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 33, habitat, SW of Cajabamba, Chimborazo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3870 m; 34, 36, host-plant Baccharis buxifolia (Lam.) Pers.; 35, usual habitat of the species occurrence along roadsides; 37, cocoon; 38, forewing (reconstructed)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261794/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF7A124D679430CA863FD3B" box="[303,334,620,644]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
), predominantly in dry tropical forest habitat (
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFF7A124D402430CAAFAFD3A" box="[852,983,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 50" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1725,1748]" captionTargetBox="[234,1357,193,1696]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1704]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 50. Stigmella species 610. 44, 46, habitat, Vilcabamba, S of Loja, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 1800 m; 45, host-plant Baccharis obtusifolia Kunth; 47, 48, leaf-mines; 49, pupa, ventral view; 50, same, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261796/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
Figs 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFF7A124D4DB430CAAFAFD3A" box="[909,983,620,645]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="44.46">44, 46</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30798E0FFF7A124D79143EFA897FD4F" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA2CB6BFFF7A124D79143EFA897FD4F" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFF7A124D79143EFA819FD17" bold="true" box="[199,308,655,680]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Remarks</emphasis>
. Description of external features are based on a single completely developed female pupa. This externally distinctive new species, associated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB0E8FFF7A124D58443D4AAEEFD72" box="[722,963,692,717]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obtusifolia">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFF7A124D58443D4AAEEFD72" box="[722,963,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Baccharis obtusifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a host-plant is left unnamed until more material will be collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
